cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the problem of transferring facial texture from one image to another in a photorealistic manner. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks and regularization techniques to preserve the identity of the original image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects of the problem. The use of regularization techniques and neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
